                <note rend="inline" type="source">360M.1121 Devenis, Michael: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-24T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 24, 1941—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2087. Michael Devenis, a naturalized American citizen, born in Lithuania, to whom
                    the Department authorized the Legation at Kaunas in July, 1940 to issue an
                    American passport, was refused permission by the Soviet authorities prior to the
                    outbreak of German-Soviet hostilities to leave Lithuania on the grounds that he
                    was a former Lithuanian citizen who had acquired Soviet nationality. He was
                    arrested in 1940 for reasons unknown to the Embassy at Moscow or to the
                    Department. Last known address: Lukishki prison, Vilna.</p>
                <p>Please endeavor to ascertain information regarding his welfare and whereabouts
                    and regarding possibility of his release and repatriation to the United States.
                    His wife and three children are in this country.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
